  "body": "### Description\n\n\"templates\" (resolving to `src/(main|test)/resources/templates`) seems to be hard-coded here: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/2.4.1.Final/extensions/qute/deployment/src/main/java/io/quarkus/qute/deployment/QuteProcessor.java#L1186\r\n\r\nThis is a bit inflexible if you have a project/module that has different kinds of templates that you want to separate from each other, e.g:\r\n```\r\nsrc/main/resources/\r\n  html-templates\r\n  pdf-templates\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to configure the base path (or even configure multiple ones?).\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
